@mli `lr_scheduler` is indeed a problem when using `retrian`, i have used a simple function https://github.com/tornadomeet/ResNet/blob/master/train_resnet.py#L9 when training resnet, so it is ok there.
but i'm not sure whether this pr will indeed fixed it and whether it will influence other part or not.  

 @taoari would you do a toy test, suppose we use `mx.lr_scheduler.MultiFactorScheduler(step=[1epoch, 3epoch], factor=0.1)`, and start training at epoch 1,2,3,4 respectively, then print out the log, we want to make sure that the logging.info log when changing `lr` is really we want . (we can use a very shallow network in minist, so this experiment will not cost). thanks!

@sbodenstein Another question I have is about the `reserveSpace`. Currently the forward and backward API calls do not share the same `reserveSpace`. https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/src/operator/cudnn_rnn-inl.h#L122-L125, https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/src/operator/cudnn_rnn-inl.h#L230-L232. However, in the CuDNN manual, it mentions that `The data in reserveSpace must have previously
been generated by cudnnRNNForwardTraining.`.
I've tried to stack two RNN symbols but the backpropagation doesn't give the correct result. I'm figuring out if it is caused by the `reserveSpace` issue.

